RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Turf CR: 91. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 63000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED TWO YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOING MOBILE pressed from outside, lost touch briefly with the leader at the eighth pole, came back on in deep stretch and got up at the wire. POTITO showed early speed and took control from MR. DREAMCYCLE early, set the pace under pressure from the outside, maintained a short lead through the bend, cleared briefly at the eighth pole, then got tested again late and was a nailed in the closing moments. GENTLEMEN'S CLUB broke a bit slow, chased off the rail then between rivals, rounded the turn two wide still between foes, finished willingly down the lane and edged HAVOC for third. HAVOC chased outside a rival then three deep, remained three wide to the stretch and missed the show. MR. DREAMCYCLE away quickly from inside, ceded command to POTITO and stalked from inside up the backstretch, saved ground inside a pair of rivals through the turn and flattened out in the late stages. MR. SUDS was off slow to begin, was green crossing over the dirt early, trailed on the inside to the stretch, moved out in the lane and failed to make an impact.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIKE OPERATOR hustled clear from outside and angled into the two path, showed the way under coaxing into and around the far turn, led two wide into the stretch, kicked clear when asked right handed and was geared down in the final sixteenth. TEMBO broke a step slow and was coaxed along after, steadied along the inside into the first turn, moved out to the two path around the bend, angled back inside on the far turn, then finished willingly to earn the place honors and whittle the gap on a geared down winner. MENDEZ MILE settled inside, saved ground through the far turn while worked on, continued up the fence in the drive and gained the show. SIGNOFTHECROSS tracked two wide into the first turn then got moved out to the four path around the bend, trailed up the backstretch, went between rivals on the second bend, came three wide into the lane and got edged for third. ECONOMICAL bobbled leaving the gate, closest early in the three path, continued to give chase three then two wide on the far turn and weakened. WARRENS CANDY MAN broke a step slow, chased two wide into the first turn then angled out and went four wide into the backstretch, rounded the far turn three to four wide and came up empty in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Tembo
ENTRY.OWNER: Tomasic Susan and Tomasic William J

HENNYS CRAZY TRAIN stalked along the rail then moved into the two path, went up to apply pressure on the backstretch, fought inside the winner through the far turn and down the lane, failed to summon the needed late kick in deep stretch but stayed on gamely to the line. PENS STREET broke a step slow, stalked three then four wide early, rounded the second bend three then two wide, kept trying in the final furlong and outfinished WHISTLER'S STYLE for third. WHISTLER'S STYLE was off a bit slow in the beginning, traveled three then four wide off the pace early, moved out widest and into contention in the middle stages, chased four then three wide on the far turn and flattened out. KUORA (PER) unhurried from inside then tipped off the rail around the clubhouse turn, continued two wide into the stretch and failed to menace. SPOILED ROTTEN dueled for the lead from inside then ceded command leaving the first turn, moved up to press the pace from inside briefly on the backstretch, dropped back on the far turn and weakened in the lane.

BIG BUZZ tucked inside at the back, steered out wide and moved into range on the backstretch, rallied four deep on the far turn, led momentarily midstretch but was outkicked by ZIMBA WARRIOR in the late stages. GOOD JUJU broke a step slow, sent from outside and vied three deep into the first turn, cleared and angled to the rail around the bend, pressured into the backstretch, cleared again at the seven-sixteenths pole, challenged outside the quarter pole, fought with outer trio to the stretch, resisted to midstretch, then relinquished the lead and yielded in the final sixteenth. SETTECENTO vied from inside into the clubhouse turn then chased GOOD JUJU briefly before having to check hard off heels approaching the three-quarter pole, went up to press between rivals, chased leaving the backstretch, re-bid at the quarter pole, fought between rivals in the stretch and weakened in the late stages. MY INDY settled two wide then along the inside, trailed on the far turn and eased out to the three path and lacked further response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRIGHT LEAF stumbled and bumped outer rival at the start, brushed two wide into the first turn, chased between rivals then got put in tight entering the far turn, tipped out to three path and started to rally under right handed encouragement, took over with a furlong remaining and kicked clear to win going away. AFJAN took a bump from inside at the start, chased three deep around the first turn, moved into the two path on the far turn, churned on down the lane and held the show. PARK CITY stalked from inside and brushed into the first turn, continued along the fence on the second bend, lacked room in upper stretch, could not find the needed response once gaining a clear path and got edged for third. ELEVADO had good early speed from inside then dueled with LOW EXPECTATIONS, inched ahead on the far turn, battled on even terms into the lane, lost command in upper stretch and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST A GUESS rated along the inside behind the top pair early, chased out of range into the far turn, continued to save ground to the stretch, rallied along the fence and overhauled NESTUCKA in the final sixteenth. NESTUCKA chased three wide around the first turn, bid four deep on the backstretch, dueled two wide on the far turn, took over in upper stretch, led into deep stretch but could not fend off JUST A GUESS late. LIGHT DRAGOON chased three to two wide then tugged forward and to attend the pace for a bit between rivals, chased again past the half-mile pole, rounded the far turn two then three wide, raced within striking distance in the furlong grounds but could not summon the needed late kick. FLEET BROTATO settled two wide then had to steady off heels on the first turn, rounded the far turn in the two path, finished willingly late and got up for a minor award. IMMELMANN dueled for command from outside, inched ahead on the backstretch, dueled again on on the far turn this time along along the rail, lost command in upper stretch, fought on to the sixteenth pole, weakened and was not persevered with late, getting nailed for a minor placing. GANTRY dueled from inside early, chased past the half-mile pole, entered the lane two wide, put in a mild bid in upper stretch but flattened out. HELEN'S SUN tracked four deep into the clubhouse turn then angled over to the two path, saved ground through the far turn and failed to menace. LONG JACKET tucked inside trailing early, saved ground through the far turn and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SANDY BOTTOM set the pace under pressure from TAMBO to the outside, shook free at the top of the stretch, roused outside the eighth pole, urged right handed midstretch and held well under steady strong handling late. TAMBO bobbled leaving the gate, went up to press SANDY BOTTOM from outside, chased that rival three wide into the lane, kept to task in the final furlong, came back on in deep stretch to gain late on the winner but needed to find more. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NYSOS dueled for command outside URBAN LEGEND, inched ahead at the quarter pole, shook free in upper stretch and asked left handed, then widened through the final furlong under strong handling and was ridden out to the wire. URBAN LEGEND dueled inside NYSOS up the backstretch and around the turn, failed to kick on with that rival in upper stretch, churned on through the final furlong and held on for second. COLORADO CRUISER attended the pace four deep early, chased the dueling pair four wide through the turn while losing ground, showed a mild response when kept to task through the lane but could not get by URBAN LEGEND for second. DE' MEDICI forwardly placed early then started to lose ground and climbed a bit on the backstretch, dropped back four wide on the turn, moved out and never quit trying in the lane and churned on for a minor award. E J WON THE CUP pressed the pace three deep early, lost ground to the top pair three wide on the turn and weakened in the lane. BRITISH ISLES climbed badly in the early stages and dropped back, went three deep into the turn, two wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. TRACKER broke in and bumped, chased the top quartet to the turn, traveled along the inside then two wide into the lane and failed to rally. BETTER THAN GOLD broke slow and got bumped by TRACKER, climbed and lacked early speed, raced along the rail then angled out on the turn, came three wide into the stretch and could not make an impact. CITADINO threw his head and leaned back to come away slow, steered down to the inside, saved ground through the turn and failed to menace. MISCHIEF MOMENTS off slow to begin, settled near the back, navigated the turn two wide and was not a factor.
